<h2 class="title">News&nbsp;</h2><hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;" /><div style="text-align: center;"><div style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-weight: bold;"></span><h3>Young Adult Book Club</h3>Come
join other young adults once a month to share the enjoyment of reading
books of all genres in a fun and casual atmosphere. Planned for those
young people in grades 8, 9 and 10. &nbsp;Meetings will occur on designated Mondays. Please contact the library
for the coordinator's name.&nbsp;<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;" /><h3>West Perth Public Library Chess Club</h3>Interested
in playing chess? &nbsp;Check out our library chess club for players of
all ages and all levels from beginner to master. &nbsp;<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold;">When</span>: Thursdays, May 5, 12 &amp; 19 from 6:30-7:30.<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;" /><h3>Summer Job Search Info Session</h3>The
Conestoga Career Centre is holding an information session to offer tips
and tricks to land your summer job. &nbsp;They will also review the
free programs and services available through Conestoga Career Centre to
support you in achieving your employment goals.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold;">When:</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Thursday, May 12, 2016 4:00 - 5:00 pm<br /><span style="font-weight: bold;">Where:</span> &nbsp; Program room @ the Library<br /><br />Please register with Conestoga Career Centre at 519-271-5700 ext. 7224 or by email at stratfordcareercentre@conestogac.on.ca<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;" /><h3>Current/Upcoming Children's Programs with PCFK<span style="font-weight: bold;"></span></h3><span style="font-weight: bold;">Mother Goose</span> - Friday mornings, 2 sessions, April 1 - May 13 (No April 22)<br />&nbsp;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- please contact Perth Care for Kids 519-348-8618
to register<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold;">Play and Read - </span>Tuesday afternoons, 2:15 - 3 pm,&nbsp; May 3 -31<br />&nbsp;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
&nbsp; &nbsp; - please contact Perth Care for Kids 519-348-8618 to
register<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold;">Shake, Wiggle and Roll</span>&nbsp;- for infants from 4-12 months<br />&nbsp;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- Friday mornings, 10:15 - 11 am, May 20 - June 10<br />&nbsp;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- please contact Perth Care for Kids 519-348-8618
to register<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;" /><h3>Spring Book Sale</h3>Mark
your calendars for this year's Spring Book Sale to be held in
conjunction with Mitchell's Town Wide Garage Sale on Saturday, May 28
from 8 am to noon.<hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;" /><h3>TD Summer Reading Club<img style="width: 241px; height: 184px; float: right;" alt="Read together" src="images/2016_Read_together_in_a_forest_or_garden_web.jpg" hspace="3" /></h3><br /><br />Visit the <a href="summer_reading.htm">TD Summer Reading Club page</a> to discover the details of the program and find the registration forms to download and print.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;" /><h3>Tweenie Tots</h3>&nbsp;This program is for young
children four years old and under.&nbsp; We have fun reading books,
playing games, singing songs and add a touch of silliness to make it a
great time.&nbsp;&nbsp;Infants are welcomed as well.&nbsp;
Children
must be accompanied by an adult.&nbsp; The program is on Thursday
mornings 10:30 -11:15 a.m.
and the donation is $1/child/session.  <span style="font-weight: bold;">&nbsp;The new session started on January 7, 2016.</span><span style="font-weight: bold;"></span></div><hr style="width: 100%; height: 2px;" /></div><span style="font-style: italic;"></span>
<div class="story"><h3><span style="font-weight: bold;"></span><span style="font-weight: bold;"></span>Do you know about &nbsp;.... our online information?
Featuring:</h3><img style="width: 150px; height: 75px; float: left;" alt="Novelist" src="images/novelist.gif" hspace="10" /><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); display: inline ! important; float: none;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Novelist</span><br />This
database allows readers to search for their favourite authors or
titles, and find others of similar interest. &nbsp;Users can browse
theme-oriented book lists at every reading level through Explore
Fiction, and look for outstanding titles in Best Fiction.<br /><br /></span><a href="http://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?authtype=ip,cpid&amp;custid=ns022607&amp;profile=novelist" style="color: rgb(58, 105, 186); font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Use in Library or online from outside of Library</a><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); display: inline ! important; float: none;"></span><br /><br /><br />
Visit the <a href="databases.htm">Online Databases
&amp; Newspapers</a> page to see all available databases.
